Problems & Pain Points
Core problem: Technical SEO auditing is often bottlenecked by expensive SaaS subscriptions with crawl limits, or relies on outdated desktop software with a steep learning curve. Why alternatives fall short:

SaaS tools (Ahrefs, Semrush) are expensive and limit the number of pages or projects you can crawl per month.
Traditional desktop crawlers (Screaming Frog) have a complex, intimidating UI that looks like a 1990s spreadsheet.
Cloud crawlers cannot easily access local development environments or sites behind firewalls. What it costs them: Wasted budget on subscription tiers they don't fully use, missed SEO errors due to crawl limits, and time wasted deciphering clunky UI. Emotional tension: Frustration with SaaS pricing models and overwhelm from overly complex data dumps.
Competitive Landscape
Direct: Screaming Frog SEO Spider — falls short because the UI is dense, outdated, and intimidating for non-technical users. Direct: Sitebulb — falls short because it can be resource-heavy and requires a recurring subscription. Secondary: Cloud SaaS Auditors (Ahrefs, Semrush, Moz) — fall short because they are expensive, have strict crawl credits, and can't crawl local/private staging environments easily.

Differentiation
Key differentiators:

Modern UI/UX: Built with React and Tailwind, featuring a sleek, intuitive dashboard (the "SaaS glow" feel) instead of a spreadsheet grid.
Local Execution: Runs locally on your machine, utilizing your own hardware and network without cloud restrictions.
Privacy-First: Crawl data is stored locally in an SQLite database, not sent to a third-party server.
Unlimited Potential: No artificial SaaS limits on projects or URLs (limited only by your machine's resources). How we do it differently: We combined the power of an enterprise-grade crawler (Crawlee) with the beautiful UI of a modern web app, packaged as a fast Electron desktop tool. Why that's better: Users get the best of both worlds: the one-time-purchase or low-cost feel of a desktop app with the slick user experience of modern SaaS. Why customers choose us: They want a simple, beautiful tool that just works, without paying hundreds of dollars a month for crawl credits.
